title: Notre Dame girls tennis team captures first District 11 title
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Notre Dame 3, Bethlehem Catholic 2 — Rapid Recap 
Notre Dame girls tennis team swept the singles spots to clinch a 3-2 win over Bethlehem Catholic on Saturday at Northwood Racquet Club and bring home the first District 11 Class AA championship in program history. 
Turning point : As soon as Bethlehem Catholic's Gabby Duffy and Tori Evert wrapped up a win at No 2 doubles to give the Golden Hawks a 2-0 lead in the team score, Notre Dame singles players Logan Lencheski , Coco Chen and Julia Mowrey swept their singles matches to deliver the title for the Crusaders. 
Top performers: Chen, Lencheski and Mowrey each had straight-set victories for Notre Dame. They only lost nine combined games in their three matches. 
What it means : The third-seeded Crusaders make school history with their first team title in program history. Chen and Lencheski won the first doubles title in team history on Monday. Notre Dame will play District 4 champion South Williamsport in the first round of the state tournament at 2 p.m. Tuesday at West Branch Tennis Club in South Williamsport. It was the first loss for Bethlehem Catholic this season.
